  "content": "t compiles**\n\nRun: `cargo build -p corvia-cli`\nExpected: compiles cleanly.\n\n**Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add crates/corvia-cli/src/workspace.rs crates/corvia-cli/src/main.rs\ngit commit -m \"feat(m2.1): implement corvia workspace status command\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 8: Workspace-Aware Search Output\n\nMake `corvia search` show which repo (namespace) each result comes from when in workspace mode.\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `crates/corvia-cli/src/main.rs` (`cmd_search` function)\n- Depends on: `SearchResult` struct in `corvia-common/src/types.rs`\n\n**Step 1: Check SearchResult fields**\n\nRead `crates/corvia-common/src/types.rs` to verify `SearchResult` includes `workstream` or enough metadata to show repo origin. The `KnowledgeEntry` already has `workstream: String` — verify `SearchResult` exposes it.\n\n**Step 2: Update search output formatting**\n\nIn `cmd_search`, after getting results, add namespace display when in workspace mode:\n\n```rust\nasync fn cmd_search(query: &str, limit: usize) -> Result<()> {\n    let config = load_config()?;\n    let is_ws = config.is_workspace();\n    // ...existing store/engine setup...\n    // ...existing search call...\n\n    for (i, result) in results.iter().enumerate() {\n        if is_ws {\n            // Show namespace (repo) origin for workspace results\n            println!(\"{}. [{}] (score: {:.4})\", i + 1, result.entry.workstream, result.score);\n        } else {\n            println!(\"{}. (score: {:.4})\", i + 1, result.score);\n        }\n        if let Some(ref file) = result.entry.metadata.source_file {\n            println!(\"   file: {}\", file);\n        }\n        // ...existing content display...\n    }\n    Ok(())\n}\n```\n\n**Step 3: Verify it compiles**\n\nRun: `cargo build -p corvia-cli`\nExpected: compiles cleanly.\n\n**Step 4: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add crates/corvia-cli/src/main.rs\ngit commit -m \"feat(m2.1): show namespace in search results for workspace mode\"\n```\n\n---\n",
